        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/36454",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "This will not work for the simple reason that the requested module is not known at bootstrap time; it is determined during routing.\r\n\r\nBootstrapping is for setting up the various dependencies necessary for the application to run. Module bootstraps are executed primarily (a) to setup autoloading, so that you can share and use resources between modules, and (b) to setup module-specific plugins.\r\n\r\nThis latter is when you should do any initialization that is module-dependent. For instance, if you need a different DB adapter or layout when a particular module is present, you would setup a routeShutdown() or dispatchLoopStarup() plugin from your module's bootstrap, that plugin would then check if the requested module matches, and then, and only then, execute those actions.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-11-24T04:15:29.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-11-24T04:15:29.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/36455",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=brunitto",
                        "name": "brunitto",
                        "displayName": "Bruno Piraj\u00e1 Moyle",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Okay, that's right.\r\n\r\nThe bootstrap should only contain calls to module's specific plugins, which in turn validates the current module - as at bootstrap time the current module is unknown.\r\n\r\nIsn't a good idea to explicitly define this behavior in the 4.6.4 reference guide section?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=brunitto",
                        "name": "brunitto",
                        "displayName": "Bruno Piraj\u00e1 Moyle",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-11-24T04:29:08.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-11-24T04:29:08.000+0000"
                }
            ]
        }
